'''Clone trooper learning helmets''' were special helmets worn by maturing [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]] grown and trained on [[Kamino/Legends|Kamino]] prior to and during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].

Learning helmets were designed in two variants: odd-class and even-class, distinguished by alternating patterns of maroon-and-cream, and plating of gold and black respectively. Cadets with even designation number wore helmets with black plating and maroon-cream-maroon pattern while odd numbered cadets wore helmets with gold plating and cream-maroon-cream pattern. These helmets were fitted with mental receptivity enhancers, to help the [[Cloning/Legends|clones]] process the massive amounts of data they received daily. Broadcast signal receivers allowed [[Kaminoan/Legends|Kaminoan]] overseers to transmit data directly into the helmets, which were synchronized to the wearer's biorhythm. Side-mounted earphones served to silence external sounds, providing an isolated audio environment in which the clone could concentrate on his learning. As these helmets were durable [[Plastoid/Legends|plastoid]] constructs, they could be worn during combat exercises.

